737 /// Update the branch weights of an exiting block of a peeled-off loop
738 /// iteration.
739 /// Let F is a weight of the edge to continue (fallthrough) into the loop.
740 /// Let E is a weight of the edge to an exit.
741 /// F/(F+E) is a probability to go to loop and E/(F+E) is a probability to
742 /// go to exit.
743 /// Then, Estimated ExitCount = F / E.
744 /// For I-th (counting from 0) peeled off iteration we set the weights for
745 /// the peeled exit as (EC - I, 1). It gives us reasonable distribution,
746 /// The probability to go to exit 1/(EC-I) increases. At the same time
747 /// the estimated exit count in the remainder loop reduces by I.
748 /// To avoid dealing with division rounding we can just multiple both part
749 /// of weights to E and use weight as (F - I * E, E).
